&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-22oct2018-1-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-22oct2018-1-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-1-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-1-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-2-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-2-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-3-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/akva-29oct2018-3-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Mostly from drawing groups at the pub (except for the Joseph Brodsky one, which was copied from a photo).</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">birds from the rspb website</title><link href="/2018/10/20/birds-from-the-rspb-website.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="birds from the rspb website" /><published>2018-10-20T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2018-10-20T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/2018/10/20/birds-from-the-rspb-website</id><content type="html" xml:base="/2018/10/20/birds-from-the-rspb-website.html">&lt;p&gt;Step 1: get pictures of birds via the RSPB’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rspb.org.uk/birds-and-wildlife/wildlife-guides/bird-a-z/&quot;&gt;Find a bird&lt;/a&gt; service (which really should be the name of an internet dating app).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Step 2: make quick copies with dip pen / Indian ink.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Step 3: crudely add watercolour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The results are hit and miss, but when it works, you get a vaguely Quentin Blake-esque look to the drawings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Success and failures presented here, featuring Aquatic warbler, Arctic skua, Arctic tern, Avocet, Balearic shearwater, Barnacle goose, Barn owl, Bar-tailed godwit, Bearded tit, Bewick’s swan, Bittern, Blackbird, Blackcap, Black grouse, Black guillemot, Black redstart, Black tern, Black-headed gull, Black-necked grebe, Black-tailed godwit, Black-throated diver, Bluethroat, Blue tit, and Brambling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/rspb-birds-1-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/rspb-birds-1-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/rspb-birds-2-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/rspb-birds-2-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus: bonus Indian ink doodle content:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/indian-ink-doodles-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/indian-ink-doodles-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Step 1: get pictures of birds via the RSPB’s Find a bird service (which really should be the name of an internet dating app).</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">do you mind if</title><link href="/2018/10/19/do-you-mind-if.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="do you mind if" /><published>2018-10-19T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2018-10-19T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/2018/10/19/do-you-mind-if</id><content type="html" xml:base="/2018/10/19/do-you-mind-if.html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/do-you-mind-if-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/do-you-mind-if-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">reconfigure 17.10.2018</title><link href="/2018/10/18/reconfigure-17-10-2018.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="reconfigure 17.10.2018" /><published>2018-10-18T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2018-10-18T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/2018/10/18/reconfigure-17-10-2018</id><content type="html" xml:base="/2018/10/18/reconfigure-17-10-2018.html">&lt;p&gt;Went along to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.summerhall.co.uk/event/life-drawing/&quot;&gt;life drawing at Summerhall&lt;/a&gt; for the first time in ages this evening. Model Xian was on a big metal scaffold that they set up on the stage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-1-1200w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-1-1200w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-2-1200w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-2-1200w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-3-1200w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-3-1200w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-4-1200w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-4-1200w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Audience during the break:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-5-1200w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/reconfigure-17oct2018-5-1200w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Went along to life drawing at Summerhall for the first time in ages this evening. Model Xian was on a big metal scaffold that they set up on the stage.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">miscellaneous drawings from this week</title><link href="/2018/10/02/miscellaneous-drawings-from-this-week.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="miscellaneous drawings from this week" /><published>2018-10-02T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2018-10-02T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/2018/10/02/miscellaneous-drawings-from-this-week</id><content type="html" xml:base="/2018/10/02/miscellaneous-drawings-from-this-week.html">&lt;p&gt;I caught a live stream of Brett Kavanaugh testifying to the Senate last Thursday. The best bits were when they called a break but the cameras kept rolling. Everyone got out their phones, journalists had chats in the corridor. Nobody seemed to realise that these mundane moments were being broadcast to the world.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/brett-kavanaugh-1-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/brett-kavanaugh-1-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/brett-kavanaugh-2-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/brett-kavanaugh-2-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My watercolour work is coming along. This is some guy dancing and throwing poses:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/dancing-man-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/dancing-man-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I got a book of David Hockney drawings out of the library. This is copied from the front cover:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/celia-wearing-checked-sleeves-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/celia-wearing-checked-sleeves-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is Norman Mailer, copied from a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/the-novel-that-norman-mailer-didnt-write&quot;&gt;photo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/norman-mailer-760w.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/img/blog/2018/norman-mailer-760w.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;alt&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">I caught a live stream of Brett Kavanaugh testifying to the Senate last Thursday. The best bits were when they called a break but the cameras kept rolling. Everyone got out their phones, journalists had chats in the corridor. Nobody seemed to realise that these mundane moments were being broadcast to the world.</summary></entry></feed>